genius.text: “Shadow People” is a song about the band’s hometown of Philadelphia, describing a period in songwriter Scott McMicken’s life when he was living in some not-so-glamorous parts of town. Scott talked about the background of the song in great depth in an interview on Bullseye with Jesse Thorn:

The artist gives a very nice sound and beat to this song, that you could dance. By the title and lyrics of this song, it could mean that the time is flying way too fast. And they wish time could be turned back. It could also mean we need to know what the lifestyle was like back then, maybe get more live.

Released in 2010 , ‘Later’ is written from the singer’s perspective , who’s waiting for a girl to acknowledge him and show interest. Instead the girl doesn’t even bother and poor guy ends up thinking that what he’s doing is so wrong and harmful for him and should stop waiting around for her. In the end though it seems that he cant stop after all and keeps waiting for her. (“I guess I really willI’ll sit around and wait for you”)
“It” is a simple song that takes on philosophically complex subject matter; namely, the philosophy of perception and reality.
